<div id="review_1248078521" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1248078521" />
    <a title="Cynda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24011982-cynda"><img alt="Cynda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1632700309p2/24011982.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1248078521?book_show_action=true">Apr 06, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cynda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cynda" href="/user/show/24011982-cynda">Cynda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24011982-cynda?shelf=history-north-american-and-usa">history-north-american-and-usa</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24011982-cynda?shelf=medical-science">medical-science</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24011982-cynda?shelf=weather">weather</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1248078521" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12545352771064118320">Updating this review of a book I read before joining Goodreads.<br/><br/>Accessible by those with basic college education, very basic meteorological concepts. This blue norther traveled through the Plain States and as far south as South Texas. The damage to property and risk to life led to a decrease in population of the Northern Plain states. Some states do not maintain the population of 50,000 that the US requires as part of the basic statehood qualifications.<br/><br/>I read this book published in 2005 because i</span>
  <span id="freeText12545352771064118320" style="display:none">Updating this review of a book I read before joining Goodreads.<br /><br />Accessible by those with basic college education, very basic meteorological concepts. This blue norther traveled through the Plain States and as far south as South Texas. The damage to property and risk to life led to a decrease in population of the Northern Plain states. Some states do not maintain the population of 50,000 that the US requires as part of the basic statehood qualifications.<br /><br />I read this book published in 2005 because in 2004 the same type of storm came through same areas. I know what happened here: snow flurries, light refraction, and a white Christmas. I wanted to know what the experience might have been like further north where the storm was worse. I did not imagine how much worse.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12545352771064118320" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
